  Layout: 5 cells west of the first `t` (cols 1-5: 1,.,2,.,3) and
  8 cells east of it (cols 7-9: 4,.,5; col 10 is tв‚‚; cols 11-13:
  6,.,7; col 14: в†ђ). Asymmetric вЂ” east is longer than west вЂ” yet
  the program halts cleanly via a chain of head-on collisions.

  Output: 1 2 4 3 2 6 5 1 7 4

  Cells
